#: ../../source/misc/email.rst:2
msgid "邮件安全"
msgstr "Email Security"

#: ../../source/misc/email.rst:5
msgid "常用概念"
msgstr "Common Concepts"

#: ../../source/misc/email.rst:6
msgid ""
"邮件安全常用的概念是SPF、DKIM和DMARC。其中 SPF (Sender Policy Framework) "
"是一条特殊的DNS记录，用于设定合法的发送邮件的IP。"
msgstr ""
"Common concepts in email security include SPF, DKIM, and DMARC. SPF "
"(Sender Policy Framework) is a special DNS record used to define the IP "
"addresses that are allowed to send mail."

#: ../../source/misc/email.rst:8
msgid ""
"DKIM (DomainKeys Identified Mail) "
"将数字签名添加到电子邮件消息的标题中，使邮件服务器拥有确保邮件内容没有更改的能力，同样DKIM也存在于DNS中。通过查询 "
"``<selector>._domainkey.example.com`` 的txt记录查询。"
msgstr ""
"DKIM (DomainKeys Identified Mail) adds a digital signature to email message "
"headers, allowing mail servers to verify that the message content has not "
"been changed. DKIM records also live in DNS and can be queried through the "
"TXT record of ``<selector>._domainkey.example.com``."

#: ../../source/misc/email.rst:10
msgid ""
"DMARC(Domain-based Message Authentication): 通过查询 "
"``<selector>._domainkey.example.com`` 的txt记录查询。"
msgstr ""
"DMARC (Domain-based Message Authentication): queried through the TXT record "
"of ``<selector>._domainkey.example.com``."
